<p>I'm using the Camel Main class to start a route from the command line.</p>  <p>What is the correct what to exit the route and the application when the processing is done?</p>  <p>Main class...</p>  <pre><code>main = new Main(); // enable hangup support so you can press ctrl + c to terminate the JVM main.enableHangupSupport(); GenericXmlApplicationContext applicationContext = new GenericXmlApplicationContext("/applicationContext.xml"); main.setApplicationContext(applicationContext); main.run(); </code></pre>  <p>Route XML</p>  <pre><code>&lt;routeContext id="VM001_incoming_context" xmlns="http://camel.apache.org/schema/spring"&gt;         &lt;route id="VM01_http_incoming"&gt;           &lt;transacted ref="mainTransactionManager"  /&gt;             &lt;from uri="bean:XMLReceiver?method=getProductData" /&gt;             &lt;convertBodyTo type="java.lang.String" /&gt;             &lt;multicast&gt;                 &lt;to uri="direct:parseXML" /&gt;             &lt;/multicast&gt;         &lt;/route&gt;         &lt;route id="VM01_parseXML"&gt;             &lt;from uri="direct:parseXML" /&gt;             &lt;bean ref="ResponseHandler" method="parseResponse" /&gt; &lt;!-- At this point I want to exit the application --&gt;         &lt;/route&gt; </code></pre>  <p>If I try try to call 'camelContext.stop()' I get this error message...</p>  <pre><code>1 inflight and pending exchanges for consumer: Consumer[bean://XMLReceiver?method=getProductData] </code></pre>  <p>Notes:</p>  <ul> <li><p>Camel 2.6 since it has to run on a Java 1.5 machine.</p></li> <li><p>I can't Ctrl+C the process, it runs over night.</p></li> <li>I don't want to call System.exit.</li> </ul>